
@startuml

class House {
  - address: string
  - buildingMaterial: string
  - hasBasement: boolean
  - basement: Basement
}

class Basement {
  - type: string
  - name: string
  - size: string
  - humidityLevel: integer (only for EarthBasement)
}

abstract class EarthBasement extends Basement {
  - humidityLevel: integer
}

abstract class ConcreteBasement extends Basement {
  - // No specific fields
}

class SemiDetachedHouse extends House {
  - hasOwnGarden: boolean
  - numberOfWindows: integer
  - hasCarportsOrGarage: boolean
  - carports: Carport
  - garage: Garage
}

class Carport {
  - isDoubleCarport: boolean
  - hasFlatRoof: boolean
}

class Garage {
  - hasAutomaticDoor: boolean
}

class Company {
  - name: string
  - address: string
}

class JobLog {
  - house: House
  - company: Company
  - hours: integer
  - price: double
}

House --|> Basement : hasBasement
Basement <|-- EarthBasement
Basement <|-- ConcreteBasement
House <|-- SemiDetachedHouse
SemiDetachedHouse "1" -- "*" Carport : has
SemiDetachedHouse "1" -- "*" Garage : has
House -- "*" Company : servicedBy
House -- "*" JobLog : hasJobLog
Company -- "*" JobLog : performsJob

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Relationships:

- **`House`** can have a **`Basement`**, which is an abstract class with two concrete subclasses: **`EarthBasement`** and **`ConcreteBasement`**.
- **`SemiDetachedHouse`** is a special type of `House`, with additional properties like `hasOwnGarden`, `numberOfWindows`, and either a `Carport` or a `Garage`.
- Each `House` is serviced by multiple `Company`s.
- A `JobLog` records a job performed by a `Company` on a `House`.

